Niger State Government will close the Minna-Bida road on September 15 to allow speedy rehabilitation work on the area. Chairman State Infrastructure Project Monitoring Committee and Chief of Staff to Governor Abubakar Bello, Balarabe Ibrahim said this in a statement yesterday in Minna. Ibrahim said the government had resolved that all articulated vehicles and heavy-duty trucks would be banned from plying the Minna-Bida road.  “The governor has directed the committee to issue an adequate notice to all road users on the proposed restriction. “In view of this, people are encouraged to prepare adequately in response to closure.” He said the governor had directed that effective from 12 midnight on September 15, movement of heavy trucks would be restricted on the state-owned roads. 